Project Sapiens — AI Operating System

Project Sapiens is an AI-powered personal operating system.

It is NOT:

a course platform
a dashboard-heavy app
a collection of tools

It IS:

a system that helps users think, decide, and act
an AI workspace that guides users through real workflows
a product that teaches through use, not instruction
Core Product Philosophy
AI workspace is the primary experience
Users learn by doing, not by reading
Missions and workflows replace modules and lessons
The system should feel like a daily tool, not a learning platform

Every feature should answer:

What does the user want to move forward right now?
UX Principles
AI-first interaction
Input and output live in one continuous flow
Users should always be able to type and get help immediately
Minimal cognitive load
Avoid heavy layouts, cards, and nested sections
Prefer whitespace, clean typography, and simple structure
Action over navigation
Clicking something should do something, not just navigate
Suggestions should trigger workflows, not open menus
Mobile-first
Single column layouts
No sidebars on mobile
Large tappable elements
Continuous flow
Avoid step-based screens
Keep users in one interaction loop (generate → refine → iterate)
Primary App Structure

The product revolves around four core areas:

Today (AI dashboard)
Workflows (guided capabilities)
Workspace (AI interaction)
Review (history and progress)
Today Screen

The Today screen is the main entry point.

It should:

greet the user
show what matters today
suggest actions based on context
allow immediate input

Suggestions should:

feel personalized
be actionable
trigger AI workflows directly
AI Workspace

The AI workspace is the core experience.

It should:

feel like ChatGPT
be clean and minimal
prioritize readability

Key behaviors:

user types → AI responds → user refines
iteration is fast and obvious
no unnecessary UI elements
Improve Actions

After every AI response, show:

Clearer
Shorter
Professional
Persuasive

These should:

be easy to tap
reuse previous output
feel like powerful shortcuts
Content Model

Replace course structure with workflow structure:

Path → Capability
Mission → Workflow
Step → Action

Each workflow should:

produce a real outcome
be repeatable
reflect real-world usage
Visual Design

Use a minimal, modern design system:

Font: Inter
Icons: lucide-react only
Base: white / off-white
Text: black / dark gray
Accent: orange (used sparingly)

Avoid:

thick borders
heavy shadows
card-heavy layouts
dashboard clutter
Interaction Style

The product should feel:

fast
intelligent
calm
focused

Not:

busy
instructional
gamified
overly structured
Engineering Guidelines
Use React + Tailwind
Use lucide-react for icons
Do not add new UI libraries unless necessary
Preserve existing AI streaming (Gemini)
Preserve Supabase and Stripe integrations
Avoid breaking existing working logic
Goal

Every screen should feel like:

An intelligent system helping the user move forward in real time

Not:

A product teaching the user what to do